365
00:19:37,166 --> 00:19:38,833
You have a good night, okay?

366
00:19:38,916 --> 00:19:41,666
Don't forget to hug it, okay?

367
00:19:45,083 --> 00:19:47,208
Huh. You're all smiles again.

368
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:56,208
It's him!

369
00:19:57,291 --> 00:19:58,583
I received your message...

370
00:19:58,666 --> 00:20:00,375
From what you describe,

371
00:20:00,458 --> 00:20:02,833
I can only conclude
that you altered the past

372
00:20:02,916 --> 00:20:05,500
and shifted the world line.

373
00:20:05,583 --> 00:20:07,708
Your scenario does
puzzle me, though.

374
00:20:07,791 --> 00:20:10,291
I don't understand how
you have retained memories

375
00:20:10,375 --> 00:20:13,791
of your original past.
It is problematic.

376
00:20:15,250 --> 00:20:16,416
I swear it's the truth...

377
00:20:16,500 --> 00:20:19,208
This has happened
to me twice now...

378
00:20:19,291 --> 00:20:21,125
What do you make of it?

379
00:20:21,208 --> 00:20:22,291
I don't know.

380
00:20:22,375 --> 00:20:24,958
In the version of 2036
from which I hail,

381
00:20:25,041 --> 00:20:26,666
the idea of using e-mail

382
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:30,333
to alter past events
hasn't been explored.

383
00:20:30,416 --> 00:20:31,833
The concept of altering the past

384
00:20:31,916 --> 00:20:35,208
and shifting the world-line
is nothing new to us.

385
00:20:35,291 --> 00:20:37,041
That said, it operates within

386
00:20:37,125 --> 00:20:38,666
limits we've
thought were absolute.

387
00:20:38,750 --> 00:20:40,500
No one has ever
been known to maintain

388
00:20:40,583 --> 00:20:45,250
their memories across world
lines and observe their changes.

389
00:20:45,333 --> 00:20:46,625
Even so...

390
00:20:46,708 --> 00:20:50,208
Kyouma... It might be
that you have that ability.

391
00:20:52,958 --> 00:20:54,750
You might be the one person...

392
00:20:54,833 --> 00:20:58,833
who can guide the world
beyond 1% divergence.

393
00:21:00,500 --> 00:21:01,333
"Guide the world?!"

394
00:21:01,416 --> 00:21:03,250
What is he talking about?!

395
00:21:06,375 --> 00:21:08,916
What is this 1% divergence
you're talking about...?!

396
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:11,833
And what lies beyond
it that's so important?!

397
00:21:28,750 --> 00:21:31,125
Beyond it lies true freedom.

398
00:21:31,208 --> 00:21:32,583
Your future is condemned

399
00:21:32,666 --> 00:21:35,583
to dystopia unless that
barrier can be crossed.

400
00:21:37,625 --> 00:21:39,583
My goal is to save the future...

401
00:21:39,666 --> 00:21:43,500
And you may be the
only one who can do it.

402
00:21:45,833 --> 00:21:48,916
You look like
you've seen a ghost.

403
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:50,083
No... It doesn't make any sense.

404
00:21:50,166 --> 00:21:51,750
This has got to be
some kind of mistake...

405
00:21:51,833 --> 00:21:54,583
How can I... save the future...?

406
00:21:54,666 --> 00:21:56,250
That's absurd...

407
00:22:07,500 --> 00:22:10,625
Kyouma... I ask you...

408
00:22:12,375 --> 00:22:14,250
...to be... our savior.

